Comment: Sicilian Defense, Wing Gambit.  I do not like this variation because black appears to enjoy a slight advantage after taking the pawn, nor do I see how white makes up for the loss with any positional gain.

White ignores the pawn for the thrill of a quick victory.  As if black could not see through such cheap parlor tricks.  Time to deploy the queen.  The beauty here is that white will no longer be able to castle, and the black queen can then traipse across the empty 5 rank to protect the h pawn.
